radiographic_examinations.findings: Atrial flutter was easily induced and then degenerated to atrial fibrillation, requiring electrical cardioversion. Linear radiofrequency lesions were delivered in the area from which flutter originated.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Neither atrial flutter nor supraventricular tachycardia could be reinduced after ablation.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Multivessel coronary artery disease was found.
